So I wonder if we could just get rid of the injection part and provide an API like this:
@Test
public void testGreet() {
   Mockito.when(MockBean.of(MessageService.class).getMessage()).thenReturn("hi");
   ...
}
... where MockBean.of() would basically do QuarkusMock.installMockForType(Mockito.mock(MessageService.class), MessageService.class) and return the mock instance (and possibly cache the instance or something like that).

