replies.bodyText:
@mkouba I agree completely about testing beans injected into a class - they are made unremovable because you are actually testing those beans.
In the mock case however, you aren't testing the injected mocks, you are testing whatever component uses the mocks - so making them unremovable should have no effect.
Am I missing something?

